                <head>No. 764<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 25, President <persName corresp="#p_EGADD1">Eisenhower</persName>
                    approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5404/1, “U.S. Policy on Berlin,”
                    which superseded <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 132/1, <ref target="#d547"
                        >Document 547</ref>. Insofar as it dealt with the German Democratic
                    Republic, the policy outlined in <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5404/1 was
                    based on an assessment of the opportunities and vulnerabilities facing the
                    Soviet Zone by virtue of Berlin’s special position. For <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5404/1, see <ref target="#d600">Document 600</ref>.</p>
            </div>
